==English==
===Noun===
'''bludger'''

# (''Australian common use slang'') A person who avoids working , or who does not do their share of work, a [[loafer]], a [[hanger on]], one who does not [[pull one's weight|pull their weight]]

====Derived terms====
*[[dole bludger]] - A person who lives off the [[dole]] ([[welfare]])

====Related terms====
*[[bludge]]

===Noun===
'''Bludger''' (''always capitalised'')

# (''Harry Potter'') The black balls used in a game of [[Quidditch]].

